# Structured Data Sync

When you change any website content that affects SEO or structured data, update the corresponding structured data if needed.

## What to check

| Content changed | Structured data to update |
|----------------|---------------------------|
| Event dates in hero sections | `src/lib/events.ts` + Event JSON-LD on city pages |
| Event list in EventsSection | `src/lib/events.ts` |
| Page title or description | `metadata` in that page or its layout |
| City/event names | `src/lib/events.ts`, page metadata |
| Site name or branding | `src/app/layout.tsx` metadata, `src/components/JsonLd.tsx` |

## Key files

- **`src/lib/events.ts`** — Central event config (dates, cities). Used by JSON-LD and sitemap.
- **`src/components/JsonLd.tsx`** — Organization and Event schema components.
- **Page layouts** — Metadata (title, description, canonical) per route.

## Example

Changing Bucharest event from "18-20 Oct" to "28-30 Oct":

1. Update `src/lib/events.ts`: `startDate: "2025-10-28"`, `endDate: "2025-10-30"`
2. Update `src/sections/EventsSection.tsx` (if it lists Bucharest)
3. Update hero section text in `BucharestHeroSection.tsx`
4. Event JSON-LD is driven by `events.ts`, so it updates automatically
